.TH RUN-MKSQUASHFS 1 "June 2026" "mx-remaster" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
run-mksquashfs \- wrap mksquashfs, capture its exit status, and record image size metadata
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B run-mksquashfs
.I status-file
.RI [ mksquashfs-options ... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B run-mksquashfs
is a small helper used by the remaster workflow when
.B mksquashfs
needs to run inside a terminal or GUI wrapper.
It executes
.B mksquashfs
with the supplied arguments, writes the exit status to the file named by the
first positional argument, and records the uncompressed filesystem size in the
live configuration metadata.

The helper also captures the command output in a temporary file so it can extract
the reported uncompressed filesystem size and write it to
.I /live/config/linuxfs.info
via the configured squashfs directory.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I status-file
Path to a file where the script will store the numeric exit code from
.BR mksquashfs .
.TP
.I mksquashfs-options
All remaining arguments are passed directly to
.B mksquashfs
without interpretation.
.SH BEHAVIOR
The script tees the mksquashfs output to a temporary file under
.IR /tmp ,
writes the command return code to the requested status file, and removes the
temporary capture file when done.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mksquashfs (1),
.BR live-remaster (1)
.SH AUTHOR
mx-remaster maintainers
